  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6 italic text-gray-300">A four-player co-op walkthrough of Halo 3: ODST (MCC version), recorded January 31, 2024 — roughly seven months after their previous session. The hosts consider it one of the best Halo games made, praising its focused single-city setting, jazz/piano soundtrack, and the spin-off format that lets it do something different from the mainline entries.</p>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">General Mechanics &amp; Observations</h2>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Grenade throw:</strong> Unique in the series — grenades go where your reticle is aimed on the horizontal plane, not where you're looking vertically. You must aim directly at the target.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Health system:</strong> No shields in the traditional sense — the equivalent is called "stamina." You still have a secondary health layer underneath.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Grenades:</strong> ODSTs can only carry <strong class="text-cyan-400">3 grenades</strong> instead of the usual 4.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Night vision:</strong> Toggle with X (default layout). The on-screen prompt to use it stops appearing after the first two missions.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Pistol:</strong> Consistently praised as the best pistol in the series. The SMG also holds up well.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Scale:</strong> ODST does a great job making the player feel smaller — Brutes appear noticeably larger and more imposing than in other Halo games.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Open world:</strong> ODST is technically the first open-world Halo game, predating Infinite by over a decade. The Mombasa Streets hub connects all missions.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">Achievements Overview</h2>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>The <strong class="text-cyan-400">majority of achievements</strong> are tied to collecting ~30 audio logs scattered across Mombasa Streets.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Important:</strong> You must actually <strong class="text-cyan-400">listen to the audio log</strong> for the achievement to unlock — picking it up is not enough.</li>
    <li>Audio logs are best collected <strong class="text-cyan-400">between the second-to-last and the final mission</strong>, as not all spawn until that window.</li>
    <li>Notable non-audio achievements include: completing a level without using Covenant weapons; keeping specific marines alive; killing 5 sleeping Grunts; Engineer-related kills (either 0 or 20); riding a Banshee; getting a Rocket Launcher to Dare; beating par scores on each mission.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Panda challenge:</strong> There is a realistic-picture panda easter egg in the environment — looking at it unlocks a campaign challenge.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">Mombasa Streets (Hub)</h2>

  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">The open hub connecting all missions. Medical kiosks provide health. Ringing phones mark audio log locations. Navigation is notoriously poor — described as "worse than Apple maps."</p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Easter Eggs</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>A <strong class="text-cyan-400">Destiny poster featuring The Traveler</strong> can be found — Bungie was already working on Destiny during ODST's development.</li>
    <li>Multiple <strong class="text-cyan-400">Halo: Reach easter eggs</strong> are present, as Reach was in development concurrently.</li>
    <li>A <strong class="text-cyan-400">Marty O'Donnell easter egg</strong> is hidden in one of the outdoor areas.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">Mission 1 – Tayari Plaza</h2>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Squad is separated at the start. The Rookie begins alone and must navigate to teammates.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Achievement:</strong> Look at a specific group of marines ("the boys") to trigger dialogue and unlock an achievement. Just approach and face them.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Jackal on second floor:</strong> There's a Jackal in an early building who reliably kills players — clear it before pushing.</li>
    <li>Hunters appear near the end. Use Spikers when available; hitting them in the back is the key weak point.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">Uplift Reserve</h2>

  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">Heavy vehicle mission. Warthog is the primary vehicle throughout.</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Banshees are a major threat and will tear apart the Warthog if ignored.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Banshee tip:</strong> You cannot jack Banshees in ODST — you must kill the pilot first to bring it down.</li>
    <li>Plasma Pistol is important for overcharging Banshees/Wraiths; keep one stocked.</li>
    <li>The Spartan Laser appears on this map and is highly effective.</li>
    <li>Multiple Scorpion tanks are available in later sections; use them against Wraiths.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">Kizingo Boulevard</h2>

  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">Street-level Scorpion tank mission — four-player chaos described as "payback time."</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Two Scorpions are available.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Achievement:</strong> Hijack a Banshee on this mission. You must kill the pilot to bring it down first.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Banshee bombing runs:</strong> Strategy: stun it repeatedly with a Plasma Pistol while someone else finishes it off.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">ONI Alpha Site</h2>

  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">Mission involves defending the ONI building; Dare gets abducted during a cutscene.</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Spartan Lasers are available and recommended.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Mickey reveal:</strong> Mickey is confirmed as the traitor in this mission — working with the insurgency/rebels, not the Covenant.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Lore note:</strong> The rebels/insurgency are still active and appear later in Halo 5 on Meridian.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">NMPD HQ</h2>

  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">Multi-floor urban building clearance.</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Marines in ODST are mortal and matter — killing them is noted as something missing from newer Halo games.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Engineers:</strong> On this mission you either kill none or aim for 20+ for the achievement split.</li>
    <li>Elevator navigation is required toward the end.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Lore note on Engineers:</strong> In Halo Wars 2, Engineers appear enslaved by the Banished, which explains why they were fighting alongside the Covenant.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">Kikowani Station</h2>

  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">Banshee-heavy section; one of the few missions where aerial combat is central.</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Banshee mechanic unique to ODST:</strong> Banshees can come to a <strong class="text-cyan-400">complete stop</strong> mid-air.</li>
    <li>To perform Banshee maneuvers, use your jump button (not the exit-vehicle button).</li>
    <li>Anti-air turrets on the ground will shoot down Banshees — clear them to maintain air superiority.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">Data Hive</h2>

  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">The "obligatory bug mission" every Halo game includes.</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Achievement:</strong> Bring a Rocket Launcher to Dare. Swap her pistol for rockets, then swap back — wait a few seconds for the achievement to register.</li>
    <li>Features the Superintendent (Virgil) as a key story element.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">Coastal Highway (Final Mission)</h2>

  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">A high-speed highway chase with Warthogs and Mongooses, escorting Virgil the Engineer.</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Virgil mechanics:</strong> He generates a shield around himself that absorbs damage. He only knows gas — no brakes. He plows through cars and obstacles with no hesitation.</li>
    <li>A <strong class="text-cyan-400">Scarab</strong> appears in this mission — stationary, taken down with a Scorpion. Noted as the easiest Scarab fight in the series because it cannot move.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Lore note:</strong> The space elevator is what fell earlier in the game's story.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">Overall Notes</h2>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Spin-off quality:</strong> The hosts consistently argue ODST and Reach are better than the mainline 343-era entries. The focused scope, grounded tone, and single-location setting are all cited as strengths.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Firefight:</strong> Several campaign maps double as Firefight maps. Sergeant Avery Johnson is a playable Firefight character.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Story vs. Halo 3:</strong> ODST is praised for its tighter character work. Halo 3 is described as a great game but primarily a "shoot-em-up" that sidelines most supporting characters.</li>
  </ul>
